&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you looking for an exciting opportunity to flourish and develop your respiratory skills working with the Neath-Port Talbot Community Respiratory Team?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic and dynamic individual who is forward thinking and proactive in delivering patient focussed care. The ethos of the team is focussed around promoting self-management and specialist care to our varying respiratory patient groups. The post holder will be required to deliver community based care to patients within their home setting. Having access to your own transport is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nathan ThomasClinical Respiratory Specialist Physiotherapist&lt;/p&gt;
